This is Perl module JSON::Pointer.

INSTALLATION

Type the following command:

    $ curl -L http://cpanmin.us | perl - JSON::Pointer

Or install cpanm and then run the following command to install
JSON::Pointer:

    $ cpanm JSON::Pointer

If you get an archive of this distribution, unpack it and build it
as per the usual:

    $ tar xzf JSON-Pointer-$version.tar.gz
    $ cd JSON-Pointer-$version
    $ perl Build.PL
    $ ./Build && ./Build test

Then install it:

    $ ./Build install

DOCUMENTATION

JSON::Pointer documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    $ perldoc JSON::Pointer

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

